SIMPLE: fecula
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fecula
<hw>fec"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>fecul⟦ae⟧</plw></plu> <ety>[L.<ets>faecula</ets> burnt tartar or
salt of tartar, dim. of <ets>faex</ets>, <ets>faecis</ets>, sediment,
dregs: cf. F. <ets>f⟦eacute⟧cule</ets>.]</ety> <def>Any pulverulent
matter obtained from plants by simply breaking down the texture, washing
with water, and subsidence.</def> <specif>Especially:</specif>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The nutritious part of wheat; starch or farina; --
called also <altname>amylaceous fecula</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>The green matter of plants; chlorophyll.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feculence</ent>⟦br⟧
